s.text: Installation--her medium--is a non-starter anyway, at best a poor cousin of window dressing or stage design, simply the wrong instrument for conveying subtle ideas visually (if her ideas are subtle).

The insistence that one must see an exhibition before having anything critical to say about ideas and images within it attributes a great importance to the visceral experience of objects, an attendance to form.
Things have pretty much come full circle if you now think that what makes Generation-Sensation so groovy is that they "graft" literary themes onto modern art.
